parameters.name: EncryptionContext
parameters.description: A JSON string that consists of key-value pairs. If you specify this parameter, an equivalent value is required when you call the Decrypt operation. For more information, see [EncryptionContext](~~42975~~).

parameters.name: KeyId
parameters.description: The globally unique ID of the CMK. You can also set this parameter to an alias that is bound to the CMK. For more information, see Use aliases.

parameters.name: KeySpec
parameters.description:
The length of the data key that you want to generate. Valid values:

*   AES\_256: 256-bit symmetric key
*   AES\_128: 128-bit symmetric key

>  We recommend that you use the KeySpec or NumberOfBytes parameter to specify the length of a data key. If both of them are not specified, KMS generates a 256-bit data key. If both of them are specified, KMS ignores the KeySpec parameter.

parameters.name: NumberOfBytes
parameters.description:
The length of the data key that you want to generate.

Valid values: 1 to 1024.

Unit: bytes.
